metadata.name: Breeding Grounds #161
metadata.description:
Social Networks.
Molecular Clouds.
Neuronal Circuitries.
Quantum Mechanical Structures.

Blurring Boundaries.
Infinite Self-Similarities.

Total.
Mess.

Perfect.
Order.

/////
Each element (besides the painting ground textures) is based on the underlying subdivided grid which is sometimes exposed like some kind of preliminary drawing.

Note on the split:
After seeing some of the outputs, Sermin had a dream about ‚ÄúBreeding Grounds‚Äù and I decided to incorporate events and feelings from her dream into the project. That's how the names of the color palettes came about. Thank you for naming them, Sermin!

Press 's' to save a .png with the current resolution (2000x3000).
If you want a file with higher resolution and/or without the ‚ÄúPainting Ground Textures‚Äù for printing please contact me via Twitter or Discord. 

/////
Created with p5.js

Twitter: @serminmin / @pxlshrd

metadata.name: Degenerative grid #4
metadata.description:
The grid, from my point of view, is an archetype of Minimal Art, this works tends to bring disruption in this rectilinear/straight design.

____

This script use 18 different palettes to create a grid in its initial stage. Then it uses random positions and Perlin noise to copy and paste parts of the grid over the existing one. In this process, it could paste sample with different modes (source-over, screen, overlay, xor & difference) and different scale (downscaling the picked sample at different sizes).Each time the program repeats the operation, it reuses the changes it has previously made.
